    <text id="F4043T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>William Tolbert asks his sister Emma to write soon and to send photographs with
                    her letter.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
             

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1865-02-25">Feb 25th/65</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sister Emma</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I wish you would write and tell me what disposition you made of the Photographs I
                    had taken when at home and if you have any at home please send me one when you
                    wrote and also <add hand="h1" place="inline">one</add> of you own and tell me
                    what the news about the town. Give my complements to Kate, Annie, &amp;
                    Emma. Write soon.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>From</salute>
                    <signed>Will</signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
